==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Modernist
<hw>Mod"ern*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>moderniste</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who admires the
moderns, or their ways and fashions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An advocate of the teaching of modern subjects, as
modern languages, in preference to the ancient classics.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>modernistic</ent>⟦br⟧
